The paper deals with an optimization problem in an ultrametric space, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves finding a median point, which is a common task in clustering and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a Monte Carlo algorithm, which is a technique often used in randomized algorithms and probabilistic analysis (cs.DM).
